cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with deep learning models for geospatial image analysis, specifically for overhead image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses methods to improve the generalizability of the models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of geostatistics and spatial analysis suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper proposes a novel feature pooling method, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category.
